I’m not sure what’s happening. You’re not on an Arm or 32-bit machine by any chance, are you? I don’t know what kind of error you’d get, but those are not supported.

If you’re on a supported rig, my best guess is a corrupt install. I would reboot to be sure no files are locked, then follow the uninstall steps (there is no uninstaller.) Then reboot again, and try reinstalling.
